---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout
  title="Resume"
  schemaType="ProfilePage"
  description="Konstantin Borovik — Software Engineer | DevOps Engineer in Toronto, Canada. 20+ years engineering. Tech skills, projects, engagements, and education."
>
  <article class="resume mx-auto max-w-3xl px-6 py-12 sm:py-16">
    <!-- Contact -->
    <header class="resume-contact">
      <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold tracking-tight text-gh-fg">Software Engineer | DevOps Engineer</h1>
      <p class="mt-4 text-base text-gh-fg-muted">Konstantin Borovik &middot; 20+ years engineering</p>
      <address class="mt-1 text-base not-italic text-gh-fg-muted">Toronto, Ontario, Canada</address>

      <ul class="resume-links mt-5 flex flex-wrap gap-x-5 gap-y-2 text-base text-gh-fg-muted">
        <li>
          <a
            href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/kborovik"
            target="_blank"
            rel="noopener noreferrer"
            class="text-gh-green hover:text-gh-green-hover underline underline-offset-[3px]">linkedin.com/in/kborovik</a
          >
        </li>
        <li>
          <a href="https://github.com/kborovik" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="text-gh-green hover:text-gh-green-hover underline underline-offset-[3px]"
            >github.com/kborovik</a
          >
        </li>
        <li>
          <a href="/" class="text-gh-green hover:text-gh-green-hover underline underline-offset-[3px]">lab5.ca</a>
        </li>
      </ul>
    </header>

    <!-- Tech skills -->
    <section class="mt-12 border-t border-gh-border pt-10">
      <h2 class="text-base font-bold uppercase tracking-[0.2em] text-gh-blue">// tech skills</h2>

      <div class="tech-stack-grid mt-8 space-y-6 text-base leading-relaxed text-gh-fg-muted">
        <div>
          <h3 class="text-base font-semibold text-gh-fg">Software Development</h3>
          <p class="mt-2">Languages: Python, TypeScript, Node.js, Bash, SQL</p>
          <p class="mt-2">Disciplines: Backend Development, Full-Stack Development, Software Architecture</p>
          <p class="mt-2">Frameworks &amp; Web: FastAPI, Pydantic, Astro, Cloudflare Workers</p>
          <p class="mt-2">APIs: REST APIs, API Design, OpenAPI, Webhooks</p>
          <p class="mt-2">Architecture: Event-Driven Architecture, Microservices, Distributed Systems, Asynchronous Programming</p>
          <p class="mt-2">Data: PostgreSQL, SQLite, Cloud SQL</p>
          <p class="mt-2">Pipelines: ETL, Data Pipelines, Structured-Extraction Pipelines</p>
          <p class="mt-2">Enterprise Integration: Salesforce Developer, Salesforce Integration, Salesforce APIs</p>
          <p class="mt-2">Testing: Pytest, Test Automation, Unit Testing</p>
          <p class="mt-2">Methodologies: Test-Driven Development (TDD), Spec-Driven Development (SDD)</p>
          <p class="mt-2">Foundations: Git, Version Control, Object-Oriented Programming</p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h3 class="text-base font-semibold text-gh-fg">DevOps</h3>
          <p class="mt-2">Google Cloud Platform (GCP): Cloud Run, Cloud Functions, BigQuery, Vertex AI, Cloud SQL, Cloud Composer, Pub/Sub</p>
          <p class="mt-2">Microsoft Azure: Azure App Service, Azure Functions, Azure Service Bus, Azure Key Vault</p>
          <p class="mt-2">Practice: DevOps, Platform Engineering, DevSecOps</p>
          <p class="mt-2">IaC: Infrastructure as Code (IaC), Terraform, Ansible, Helm</p>
          <p class="mt-2">Containers: Docker, Kubernetes, Google Kubernetes Engine (GKE), Azure Kubernetes Service (AKS), Container Orchestration</p>
          <p class="mt-2">CI/CD: Continuous Integration, Continuous Deployment, GitHub Actions, Azure DevOps</p>
          <p class="mt-2">Orchestration: Apache Airflow, Workflow Orchestration</p>
          <p class="mt-2">Systems: Linux, Shell Scripting, YAML</p>
          <p class="mt-2">Observability: Observability, OpenTelemetry, Pydantic Logfire, GCP Cloud Logging, GCP Log Analysis</p>
          <p class="mt-2">Security &amp; Compliance: Cloud Security, Secrets Management, Identity and Access Management (IAM), NIST 800-53, PCI DSS</p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h3 class="text-base font-semibold text-gh-fg">AI &amp; LLM</h3>
          <p class="mt-2">Agents: Agentic AI Development, AI Agents, AI Engineering</p>
          <p class="mt-2">Models &amp; APIs: Large Language Models (LLM), LLM Integration, Anthropic Claude, Anthropic API, Google Gemini</p>
          <p class="mt-2">Tooling: Pydantic AI, Model Context Protocol (MCP), Retrieval-Augmented Generation (RAG), Prompt Engineering</p>
          <p class="mt-2">AI-Augmented Development: Claude Code, Claude Skills, AI-Augmented Development</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Projects -->
    <section class="mt-12 border-t border-gh-border pt-10">
      <h2 class="text-base font-bold uppercase tracking-[0.2em] text-gh-blue">// projects</h2>

      <div class="mt-8 space-y-6">
        <article>
          <h3 class="text-base font-semibold">
            <a
              href="https://github.com/kborovik/mailpilot"
              target="_blank"
              rel="noopener noreferrer"
              class="text-gh-green hover:text-gh-green-hover underline underline-offset-[3px]"
              >github.com/kborovik/mailpilot</a
            >
          </h3>
          <p class="mt-1 text-base leading-relaxed text-gh-fg-muted">
            Pydantic AI agent for business email &mdash; LLM workflows on a Google Cloud backend; live at demo@lab5.ca.
          </p>
        </article>

        <article>
          <h3 class="text-base font-semibold">
            <a
              href="https://github.com/kborovik/gcp-devops"
              target="_blank"
              rel="noopener noreferrer"
              class="text-gh-green hover:text-gh-green-hover underline underline-offset-[3px]"
              >github.com/kborovik/gcp-devops</a
            >
          </h3>
          <p class="mt-1 text-base leading-relaxed text-gh-fg-muted">
            Reference Terraform / Ansible / IaC patterns for Google Cloud &mdash; Cloud Run, Pub/Sub, observability.
          </p>
        </article>

        <article>
          <h3 class="text-base font-semibold">
            <a
              href="https://github.com/kborovik/pilot-skills"
              target="_blank"
              rel="noopener noreferrer"
              class="text-gh-green hover:text-gh-green-hover underline underline-offset-[3px]"
              >github.com/kborovik/pilot-skills</a
            >
          </h3>
          <p class="mt-1 text-base leading-relaxed text-gh-fg-muted">
            Claude Code skills SDK plugins &mdash; spec-driven development and agentic workflows.
          </p>
        </article>

        <article>
          <h3 class="text-base font-semibold">
            <a
              href="https://github.com/kborovik/lab5.ca"
              target="_blank"
              rel="noopener noreferrer"
              class="text-gh-green hover:text-gh-green-hover underline underline-offset-[3px]"
              >github.com/kborovik/lab5.ca</a
            >
          </h3>
          <p class="mt-1 text-base leading-relaxed text-gh-fg-muted">
            This site &mdash; Astro 6, Tailwind v4, TypeScript, Cloudflare Workers; spec-driven, deploy on push.
          </p>
        </article>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Engagements -->
    <section class="mt-12 border-t border-gh-border pt-10">
      <h2 class="text-base font-bold uppercase tracking-[0.2em] text-gh-blue">// engagements</h2>

      <div class="mt-8 space-y-10">
        <article>
          <div class="flex flex-wrap items-baseline justify-between gap-x-4">
            <h3 class="text-base font-semibold text-gh-fg">lab5.ca</h3>
            <span class="text-base text-gh-fg-muted">2026 &mdash; present</span>
          </div>
          <p class="mt-1 text-base font-medium text-gh-fg">Independent Contractor &middot; Software Engineer | DevOps Engineer</p>
          <p class="mt-3 text-base leading-relaxed text-gh-fg">
            lab5.ca is my independent consulting practice with client engagements across AI &amp; LLM engineering,
            DevOps &amp; Cloud Platform Engineering, and modern software development. I take systems from prototype to
            production: designing agentic architectures, writing the Infrastructure as Code that runs them, and
            building the developer tooling that keeps them shipping.
          </p>
          <p class="mt-3 text-base font-medium text-gh-fg">What I deliver:</p>
          <ul class="mt-3 space-y-3 text-base leading-relaxed text-gh-fg-muted">
            <li class="flex gap-3">
              <span class="text-gh-fg-muted">&minus;</span>
              <span
                >AI &amp; LLM engineering &mdash; production agentic systems on Anthropic Claude and Google Gemini
                (Pydantic AI, multi-agent orchestration, structured-extraction pipelines), Claude Code plugins and
                skills for developer workflows, Model Context Protocol (MCP) integrations, prompt engineering, and
                LLMOps practices for AI applications.</span
              >
            </li>
            <li class="flex gap-3">
              <span class="text-gh-fg-muted">&minus;</span>
              <span
                >DevOps &amp; Cloud Platform Engineering &mdash; Terraform across the full Google Cloud spectrum
                (GKE, GCE, Cloud SQL, networking, firewalls, IAM, org policies), Helm for Kubernetes release
                pipelines, CI/CD via GitHub Actions and Azure DevOps, Cloud Composer / Apache Airflow for ETL
                orchestration, and observability with OpenTelemetry and Pydantic Logfire.</span
              >
            </li>
            <li class="flex gap-3">
              <span class="text-gh-fg-muted">&minus;</span>
              <span
                >Software development &mdash; Python and TypeScript backends and full-stack web applications
                (FastAPI, Pydantic, Astro, Cloudflare Workers), PostgreSQL data layers, REST APIs, event-driven
                architectures, and Salesforce integration.</span
              >
            </li>
          </ul>
        </article>

        <article>
          <div class="flex flex-wrap items-baseline justify-between gap-x-4">
            <h3 class="text-base font-semibold text-gh-fg">Colliers International</h3>
            <span class="text-base text-gh-fg-muted">2023 &mdash; 2025</span>
          </div>
          <p class="mt-1 text-base font-medium text-gh-fg">Software Engineer</p>
          <p class="mt-3 text-base leading-relaxed text-gh-fg">
            I built and operated data integration pipelines connecting Salesforce to enterprise business applications
            across a two-cloud environment &mdash; Google Cloud and Microsoft Azure. ETL was orchestrated on Google
            Cloud Composer (managed Apache Airflow), backed by PostgreSQL for workflow state and Cloud Storage for
            staging and archival.
          </p>
          <ul class="mt-3 space-y-1.5 text-base leading-relaxed text-gh-fg-muted">
            <li class="flex gap-3">
              <span class="text-gh-fg-muted">&minus;</span>
              <span
                >Salesforce data integration &mdash; bidirectional pipelines syncing accounts, opportunities, and
                operational data between Salesforce and downstream business applications via the Salesforce APIs</span
              >
            </li>
            <li class="flex gap-3">
              <span class="text-gh-fg-muted">&minus;</span>
              <span
                >Cross-cloud ETL on Cloud Composer / Apache Airflow &mdash; idempotent, self-recovering Python DAGs
                moving data between sources in Google Cloud and Microsoft Azure; PostgreSQL for workflow state, Cloud
                Storage for intermediate data, replacing manual transfers end-to-end</span
              >
            </li>
            <li class="flex gap-3">
              <span class="text-gh-fg-muted">&minus;</span>
              <span
                >CI/CD pipelines via Azure DevOps and Infrastructure as Code via Terraform on Google Cloud &mdash;
                Composer environments, GCS buckets, Cloud SQL, IAM, networking, and automated test/deploy for DAGs and
                supporting services</span
              >
            </li>
          </ul>
        </article>

        <article>
          <div class="flex flex-wrap items-baseline justify-between gap-x-4">
            <h3 class="text-base font-semibold text-gh-fg">PayPal</h3>
            <span class="text-base text-gh-fg-muted">2018 &mdash; 2023</span>
          </div>
          <p class="mt-1 text-base font-medium text-gh-fg">DevOps Engineer</p>
          <p class="mt-3 text-base leading-relaxed text-gh-fg">
            I wrote Infrastructure as Code and Kubernetes release tooling supporting deployment and operations of a
            large application microservices estate on Google Cloud, under NIST-800-53 and PCI-DSS controls.
          </p>
          <ul class="mt-3 space-y-1.5 text-base leading-relaxed text-gh-fg-muted">
            <li class="flex gap-3">
              <span class="text-gh-fg-muted">&minus;</span>
              <span
                >Terraform across the full Google Cloud infrastructure spectrum &mdash; GKE clusters, GCE instances,
                Cloud SQL, VPC networking, firewall rules, load balancers, IAM, service accounts, and org policies</span
              >
            </li>
            <li class="flex gap-3">
              <span class="text-gh-fg-muted">&minus;</span>
              <span
                >Helm charts and release pipelines for the application platform &mdash; deployment, configuration, and
                lifecycle management for a large fleet of microservices on GKE, serving 20+ backend engineering
                teams</span
              >
            </li>
            <li class="flex gap-3">
              <span class="text-gh-fg-muted">&minus;</span>
              <span
                >Secrets management and security controls satisfying NIST-800-53 and PCI-DSS &mdash; IAM design,
                firewall and network policies, encrypted secrets handling, and audit-ready infrastructure</span
              >
            </li>
          </ul>
        </article>

        <article>
          <div class="flex flex-wrap items-baseline justify-between gap-x-4">
            <h3 class="text-base font-semibold text-gh-fg">CDW</h3>
            <span class="text-base text-gh-fg-muted">2010 &mdash; 2018</span>
          </div>
          <p class="mt-1 text-base font-medium text-gh-fg">DevOps Engineer &middot; Platform Engineer</p>
          <ul class="mt-3 space-y-1.5 text-base leading-relaxed text-gh-fg-muted">
            <li class="flex gap-3">
              <span class="text-gh-fg-muted">&minus;</span>
              <span>Python automation tooling for cloud migration and deployment across client engagements</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex gap-3">
              <span class="text-gh-fg-muted">&minus;</span>
              <span>Led a team automating enterprise infrastructure provisioning and platform operations</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex gap-3">
              <span class="text-gh-fg-muted">&minus;</span>
              <span
                >NetApp storage, VMware virtualization, FortiGate firewalls &mdash; enterprise infrastructure stack
                across client engagements</span
              >
            </li>
          </ul>
        </article>

        <article>
          <div class="flex flex-wrap items-baseline justify-between gap-x-4">
            <h3 class="text-base font-semibold text-gh-fg">TD Bank Financial Group</h3>
            <span class="text-base text-gh-fg-muted">2003 &mdash; 2009</span>
          </div>
          <p class="mt-1 text-base font-medium text-gh-fg">Systems Engineer</p>
          <ul class="mt-3 space-y-1.5 text-base leading-relaxed text-gh-fg-muted">
            <li class="flex gap-3">
              <span class="text-gh-fg-muted">&minus;</span>
              <span>Datacenter operations across Dell &amp; IBM servers and Windows Server fleets</span>
            </li>
          </ul>
        </article>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Education -->
    <section class="mt-12 border-t border-gh-border pt-10">
      <h2 class="text-base font-bold uppercase tracking-[0.2em] text-gh-blue">// education</h2>
      <article class="mt-6">
        <div class="flex flex-wrap items-baseline justify-between gap-x-4">
          <h3 class="text-base font-semibold text-gh-fg">Northern Alberta Institute of Technology</h3>
          <span class="text-base text-gh-fg-muted">2000 &mdash; 2002</span>
        </div>
        <p class="mt-1 text-base text-gh-fg-muted">Network Engineering Technology</p>
      </article>
    </section>
  </article>

  <style is:global>
    @media print {
      @page {
        size: letter;
        margin: 0.5in 0.55in;
      }
      html {
        font-size: 10px !important;
      }
      body {
        background: #ffffff !important;
        color: #000000 !important;
      }
      body > header,
      body > footer {
        display: none !important;
      }
      main {
        padding: 0 !important;
      }
      .resume {
        max-width: 100% !important;
        padding: 0 !important;
        margin: 0 !important;
      }
      .resume,
      .resume p,
      .resume li,
      .resume span,
      .resume address,
      .resume ul,
      .resume a,
      .resume div {
        font-size: 1rem !important;
        line-height: 1.4 !important;
      }
      .resume h1 {
        font-size: 1.6rem !important;
        line-height: 1.15 !important;
        margin: 0 !important;
      }
      .resume h2 {
        font-size: 1.05rem !important;
        line-height: 1.2 !important;
        letter-spacing: 0.18em !important;
        margin: 0 !important;
      }
      .resume h3 {
        font-size: 1.3rem !important;
        line-height: 1.2 !important;
        margin: 0 !important;
      }
      .resume article > div + p {
        font-size: 1.1rem !important;
        line-height: 1.25 !important;
      }
      .resume article > div > span {
        font-size: 0.9rem !important;
        color: #57606a !important;
      }
      .resume a {
        color: #000000 !important;
        text-decoration: none !important;
      }
      .resume .border-t {
        border-color: #d0d7de !important;
      }
      .resume .mt-12 {
        margin-top: 1.5rem !important;
      }
      .resume .pt-10 {
        padding-top: 1rem !important;
      }
      .resume .mt-8 {
        margin-top: 0.75rem !important;
      }
      .resume .mt-5 {
        margin-top: 0.25rem !important;
      }
      .resume .mt-4 {
        margin-top: 0.2rem !important;
      }
      .resume .mt-3 {
        margin-top: 0.15rem !important;
      }
      .resume .mt-2 {
        margin-top: 0.1rem !important;
      }
      .resume .mt-1 {
        margin-top: 0.05rem !important;
      }
      .resume .py-12,
      .resume .sm\:py-16 {
        padding-top: 0 !important;
        padding-bottom: 0 !important;
      }
      .resume .space-y-10 > :not([hidden]) ~ :not([hidden]) {
        margin-top: 0.5rem !important;
      }
      .resume .space-y-6 > :not([hidden]) ~ :not([hidden]) {
        margin-top: 0.5rem !important;
      }
      .resume .space-y-1\.5 > :not([hidden]) ~ :not([hidden]) {
        margin-top: 0.05rem !important;
      }
      .resume .tech-stack-grid {
        display: grid !important;
        grid-template-columns: 1fr !important;
        row-gap: 0.5rem !important;
      }
      .resume section,
      .resume article,
      .resume .tech-stack-grid > div {
        break-inside: avoid;
      }
      .resume section {
        margin-top: 0.8rem !important;
        padding-top: 0.5rem !important;
      }
      .animate-on-scroll,
      .animate-hero {
        opacity: 1 !important;
        transform: none !important;
        animation: none !important;
      }
    }
  </style>
</Layout>
